caption: Unfortunate, it was a soggy oily mess. My girlfriend used to love this place and we were disappointed to find the quality has dropped since 2 years ago
Great pizza and wonderful staff, but I really miss their Hamm’s beer! No one else in DC had it. Please bring it back!
Shirley for life!!
The service was quick and polite. The pizza was hot. The flavor of the pizza was not very good. Flavorless.

This pizza is top notch. The crust is crisp enough to hold up toppings, but thin enough to fold: the perfect balance. Great cheese and sauce ratio. The spicy honey is a unique topping option too. And the staff are lovely! Highly recommend.

The customer service is excellent. Staff are very friendly. The restaurant looked clean and everything else was great... except the pizza. I was really excited to try this place because of all the great reviews. But the pizza was not good at all. We tried the Cheese and the Penelope. The cheese was better but still not good. To be fair, we ordered take out. It's possible that it'll taste better if you eat it when it comes straight out of the oven instead of 15-20 minutes later.

Just had this pizza and it was good but sadly all three pizzas were burnt. The first two weren’t terribly bad and I don’t mind a little burnt but the third pizza was really burnt. I didn’t really care however looking at my receipt I noticed that they charged a $8 tip , not sure why I had to pay tip to go inside and pick up my own pizza. Anyways I would just make sure to check the pizza before leaving to make sure it isn’t burnt . The margarita pizza was amazing by the way!
Awesome service as always!!
Excellent pizza, fun atmosphere, great neighborhood, and delicious weekend breakfast menu.

Craving wood-fired pizza during Covid-19? Timber is the way to go is super fast online ordering! While Timber is typically a zoo full of elbow-rubbing, it's impressively sanitary with no crowds during Covid. All the kitchen workers and staff members wear masks and gloves - so your precious pizza is protected!  You can order on the phone or online just not in-person, which is a great way of eliminating lines. Easy grab and go!  We ordered 2 Cheese Please and they were ready in 10 minutes pipping hot. I picked up the pizzas right outside the tent as the restaurant is closed off.  The "Cheese Please" hit the spot with a soft pillowy charred crust, globs of fresh mozzarella cheese and sweet tomato sauce baked to perfection in a 800 degree wood-fired oven.  The scrumptious pizza is well worth the trek from McLean - we come at least a month and been over 1/2 dozen times since Covid!  Excited to come back for some more pies with no wait times!

Wow - amazing pizza! Cheese and toppings are excellent quality and the crust is chewy but firm. We tried The Shirley and it was made quickly; even though it had many toppings they were added with nuance and care that greatly improved the flavor combinations. If you want novelty pizza in DC, this must be near the top of your list!
Deliciously fast
(Translated by Google) Delicious on the palate.  (Original) Delicioso al paladar.
So good!!

Docked a star due to inability to presently  pay in person (by cash or card).  Only way to presently order is via online or calling in and they take your credit card over the phone (even if you are standing right outside).  Can understand and respect contactless payment due to pandemic to minimize risk but perhaps accept Apple Pay, Samsung Pay and Google Pay exclusively for in person transactions as an option to and for those that want to walk up and purchase but did not call ahead.  Was first time here and was excited to try due to favorable reviews had heard.  "2" hungry adults will definitely need at least two pizza pies.  Decent pricing but reset assured not cheapest option in town for pizza.  Tasty pies and both myself and SO thoroughly enjoyed ours (even with some leftovers for following day).  Swift takeout business evening we were there with seemingly people arriving every 3-5 min to pick up an order (many of which walking up indicating to me that they were local).  Would recommend and plan to return and will simply be sure to order online in advance this time around.
OMG the food here is incredible and I highly recommend you try these guys out. Love everything about their food and it great for a family game night.
Great pizza especially if you love thin pizza. Great sauce to crust to cheese ratio. Definitely what I would call "fancy pizza" - hits the spot!

Great pizza, particularly the quality of toppings and cheese, I wish the crust had more structure and flavor, but the soft chewy texture was lovely and the fire-baked aroma is nice. I've also tried the breakfast empanadas, which are fine, and the bagels, which are good. Nothing spectacular but it's great for DC. Also they clearly take pride in the freshness and balance of their salads, so I can recommend those full-heartedly!
Timber really $h!+ the bed tonight. 30 people standing around waiting for pre-orders. Lost on-line orders.30-45 minutes behind.
The best pizza I've tasted.
This pizza is to die for. Yum!
Good pizza and solid price

Just ate there, they are amazing, the food is very fresh, they use alot of local farm stuff, we miss ordered thinking we ordered three pizzas, they gave us a free pizza because our friend came from Kazakhstan just to try their pizza... amazing staff and great food, my fav. Pizza place in DC from now on.
Great pizza flavor...Quick service staff and nice. Recommended!
Pretty good Neapolitan style pizza, just skip the salads.
We had a delicious pizza here, the sauce and the toppings was amazing. Great staff and good customer service. Definitely recommended!
This pizza is out of this world good! Definitely will be back!
Easy to order from their website and fast pickup. Love the Lulu
Best pizza in DC, better than 2 Amy's. With every penny.
Best Gluten-Free pizza in the city

I've lived in D.C. for thirteen years, frequent the food scene and somehow it took me until now to have Timber Pizza Company, one of the most beloved pizza spots in Washington, D.C. Here's what's to love:  1) The location is on a fun street in Petworth with other great businesses like Loyalty Books, Ciner BBQ, She Loves Me, etc. As you wait to be seated or do pick-up, you can wander the streets. There's a fun art space called Art of Noize behind Timber.  2) The pizza was good. I ordered the Bentley and thought the flavors complimented each other well. The dough was excellent. However, I thought my pizza would have a more powerful flavor to it. It was good, but it didn't change my life.  3) The staff is excellent- friendly, helpful and just cool.  I'd recommend Timber Pizza to people!
Great brick oven pizza 👌
Worst pizza I’ve ever eaten.

WOW! Finally tried this place last week and was blown away by how good their pizza's are.  The adults had the Bentley and it was really good.  The kids had the Pretty in Pepperoni and I may have liked it more!  And thats rare for just a pepperoni pie.  Crusts were amazing, toppings were great.  I really liked the red sauce on the PiP.  Wish I had a picture to show off but it all vanished super fast.  Also a tasty salad the Daryl it looks like.  And thats from a mea-tarian...:)
They came to our neighborhood and gave me some of the best pizza I've ever had.
Absolutely incredible pizza, best I have had in DC
LOVE LOVE LOVE. Will be back. Maybe today.
Always a baller experience. The best.
Best deep dish PIZZA in Washington D.C Mozzarella was soft and melty. Crust was perfect and tasty.

Gluten free pizza here is legit, they accommodate for wheat allergy but please call ahead if you have celiacs concerns. they seems very friendly towards this and will do their best, like most places you eat out at, it's at your own discretion/risk. but it's extremely rare that you'll find a place that actually does accommodate. And I thank Timber Pizza Company for this.
Absolutely loved the pizza & vibe here! It’s a popular joint so get there early to ensure a table. Service wasn’t super friendly but it was efficient. The pizzas were delicious! ❤️🍕
Great pizza and amazing service, the only thing is prices are high.

(Translated by Google) Although very tasty pizza !! Worth a try. The space is beautiful. If the weather is good you can sit in the tables outside. It may be a bit far from the highlights but its worth the pizza and of course the space you enjoy. The staff were polite and the service impeccable !!  (Original) Παρά μα παρά πολύ γευστική πίτσα!! Αξίζει να τη δοκιμάσεις. Ο χώρος είναι όμορφος. Αν έχει καλό καιρό μπορείς να κάτσεις στα τραπεζάκια έξω. Μπορεί να είναι λίγο μακριά από τα κεντρικό σημεία αλλά αξίζει πολύ η πίτσα του και φυσικά ο χώρος που την απολαμβάνεις. Το προσωπικό ήταν ευγενικό και η εξυπηρέτηση άψογη!!
Visited during my last stay in DC,  and will be going back on my next!! Absolutely the best!!

My family and I came here to celebrate my birthday. They do not take me reservations but that wasn't an issue on a Sunday night. We waited about 15 to 20mins before we were seated. We started off with a filling salad that had a unique and light dressing. We then went overboard and ordered 5 different pizzas. All of them had different flavors that were absolutely delicious but I definitely stuffed myself. 1. The D & D 2. The Shirley 3. Green Monster 4. Cheese Please 5. The Ackley
Amazing pizza, quick yet friendly service

This was such a gem! We went here a couple years back, because it was the closest from our Airbnb. Then three years ago a friend from DC took me here and I realized I had already been. This is a great restaurant. The food is amazing and the atmosphere is just vining and harmonic. I will always come back for that pizza.
Great pizza -- gets a little crowded and hectic inside, but its worth it. Definitely will be back.
Great pizza, a little pricey but yummy. Friendly staff!

Love to support a neighbor business, especially one that's so hyped. Unfortunately, I wasn't terribly impressed with my gluten free pizza. First of all, it's important to note that they make their own gluten free crust and don't use one of the 2 mainstream brands most others places do. For this, there is a $4 upcharge. This is a bit more than other places, but not unreasonable. However, I didn't love the gluten free crust itself. It was soggy and lacking flavor. The toppings and overall flavor profile were great, which more than made up for it. Even though I didn't love it, I'll be back and hope that will time come some minor improvements
Omg the best pizza I have ever had in my life!!!!!!

First review of 2020. Timber has been on my shortlist since I moved to DC in October. While debating takeout tonight, I decided to skip mediocracy.  Easy street parking but very busy inside. The space is quite small so be prepped to snag anything open, wait or grab and go.  We opted to try The Lot and Pretty in Pepperoni. Both were outstanding and delicious in their own way. Flavors were bold but not overpowering and the crust was light and airy.  Will be back soon! Can't wait to try more.
One of my favorite pizzas in the city. Great service friendly and quick.

Without a doubt the best pizza in town! I love the cheese pizza as its perfectly simple and comes with fresh basil. The Green Monster is also a winner with a pesto sauce and lots of veggies on top. Timber has gotten popular over the last year, but you should believe the hype. Sometimes it’s hard to snag a seat but if you’re lucky you can find something at the bar or outside.  In addition to their pizza, they also have an amazing breakfast. Their bagel sandwiches are the perfect weekend treat.  The only negative about this place is that they are closed on Mondays and In the afternoon on Friday and Saturday. Other than that, this place is perfect!

They even have vegan cheese!  And you would think that would turn the whole thing around... make it a terrible pizza... blasphemous even.  But it doesnt!  This lil shop really isn't leaning on the cheese to make their pizzas so delicious. Every ingredient that participates is amazeballs.  Everyone usually goes for the Bentley which is in fact pretty dope.  But that Penelope is also a jam
Expect it to be packed around dinner but it's well worth the wait.
Rude reception! We were rudeley turned away ... so no idea how the pizza is, but likely won't return to find out ...
Excellent pizza every single time! Go!
Decent pizza but not worth the super long wait.

Timber Pizza Company: 9/10 I eat and review pizza literally every week, this is the only occasion I felt I could eat an entire second pizza. It's just that good folks. The balance of this pizza is really unmatched.  Follow the @pizzaquestdc on instagram and twitter if you dont believe me.
My favorite pizza in DC. It's always busy, but you still get fast and good service. Good selection of drinks while you wait for your pizza.

Great pizza! The idea is great, make sure to come off peak hours. This place is always packed! It proved why its that good!  We had the green Monster and Bentley. Simply delicious. Lots of drink options. Love their choices. Will definitely come back.
Morning empanadas and evening pizza, so you grab a good bite before and after work.
Best pizza in DC. You usually need to wait in line, but trust the process. The salads are good and a small one is plenty for two people.

The pizza is solid but I don't think it's anything extraordinary. It's great that they offer gluten free crust options which is very welcome.  The taste of the toppings are great but the crust doesn't rate among the best pizzas I've ever had.
Amazing pizza !!!
The pizza is absolutely delicious. Good customer service, as well.
Very tasty pizza with interesting options. We tried a bunch of different types, my favorite was the Penelope. A hungry person could easily eat a whole pizza. I only wish that I lived closer!
Pizza was exceptional. Fresh and delicious.
Small place, very busy. Great pizza.
Always high quality food. Pizzas can be a little pricey.

A definite favorite. It starts with a great crust and ends with some interesting toppings, and you get choices of sauces ranging from red to white to green. I've never had a bad bite here. And often get every pizza 1/2 and 1/2 because I can't decide and want to try everything (some pizzas change, seasonally and I've had everything from roasted corn to pork to nectarines on them).  Order at the counter FIRST and wait for a table to open up. Don't be afraid to join other people at a table if you're a small party. It's a tiny place, but it's comfortable and casual and family style seating works well here for a communal experience.
Great vibes, even better pizza!

One of the best pizza places in DC. I would go multiple times a week if carbs weren't the devil.  Pizza - Great crust, just the right amount of crunch. - Sauce is pretty good, not too sweet - Toppings are amazing, I normally get the Bentley which has sopressatta, cheese-cured chorizo, peppers and honey. This is one of the greatest topping combinations I've ever tasted.  Empanadas - I had the brisket/pastrami empanadas, I really enjoyed them but I'm not really an empanadas enthusiast. The spicy pineapple dipping sauce is really good as well.  The service is amazing, there is a really good selection of beer as well. I would highly recommend this place at least once if you love pizza. The lines can be a bit long and it's not the cheapest pizza but I think it's worth it.
Amazing pizza overall. I think this is one of the best DC pizza spots.

Went here on a date and this place will allow you to be your most awkward you. The waiting area is you standing over other patrons as they eat. Community benches for seating that only allow you to have one body part on it at a time.  Playlist was great.  It's like if Zpizza and Whole Foods had a baby and then Starbucks baristas raised it.  Nice decor.  The pizza was very good.

Low-key, friendly place with delicious pizza- definitely some of the best I've had in DC! The menu has tons of great options and you can get half-and-half if, like me, you can't decide. I had a pizza with The Green Monster (a pesto pizza) and The Lucy (a white pizza) and both were excellent. It's a small place with a few larger tables and a full service bar, which is where we sat. The drink selection was great and both drinks and food came quickly. We will definitely come back!

Great pizza in a cute space! It is small, so be ready to wait for a table to open up, but you order first and the food comes quickly so the wait won't be bad (there are also bar seats if you want drinks).  The pies are a good size for one person with a couple slices for leftovers. The ingredients are fresh and the dough is nice and chewy. Overall awesome place!
t GOD for timber pizza co.... really the only good pizza imo in DC. Their empanadas and salads are also good.
Great pizza!
This is the best pizza I've ever eaten. I always eat here when in NW DC.  Small but worth the wait.
Best pizzas in town for sure!
Best wood fired pizza in the DC. The Bently and Pepperoni are my two favs. Beware lines can be long but move rather efficiently.
Amazing food, will return!!
So good! The short wait is always worth it
Best breakfast empanadas ever 🤞
Delicious and well worth the wait.
Best pizza in DC
This place is hands down the best pizza in DC.
Empanadas were great!

The place was cozy and had a good selection of pizzas, but all in one size though. The pizzas were very lite and tasty. The green monster was really tasty. We did two different types half and half. The staff was friendly and the place has a very good lighting.
This restaurant offers health insurance to employees working 30 hours or more.
My fiancé and I love this pizza. We just wish it was closer to downtown.  I appreciate their small bar for some draft beers. I would easily recommend this pizza.

I popped out of the Metro 🚇 at McPherson Square Station into the Farmfresh By the White House Farmers Market. I was having a hard time deciding because everything looked so good. I ended up going with Timber Pizza Company though. I mean how many vendors haul a huge pizza oven with them to bake fresh pizzas. The workers were fast and cheery, which always makes for a more pleasant experience. Back to the food though.  The Green Monster pizza was amazing: Pesto, mozzarella, feta, kale, and zucchini! 🤤 I’ve only had a handful of pesto pizzas, but this has been the best one so far. Really good flavor and the crust was soft and perfectly baked. Would totally eat this again. Although, I may be tempted to try one of each pizza. 🍕 No need to hold back on a good thing, right? I’m not from the area so I don’t know if they’re at the farmers market every week, but market is open Thursdays 11:00-2:00 and is located at 810 Vermont Ave NW. I’m not sure when I’ll be back in the area, but I hope to be here on Thursday. 😃
Food is always great, staff are hard working and friendly, fun neighborhood spot that is TOO popular
I don't understand all the fuss about this pizza, it's good as it should be but didn't rock my pizza world 🤔.  For the money La Villa Pizza on 14th St. NW makes a great pie and delivers.  3.5 stars.

Timber Pizza did an excellent job catering the wedding. They had no problem setting up bars in both the cocktail hour and reception areas. From what I could tell, no guest was waiting for food and Timber was kind enough to box up leftovers at the end of the night.  They did an excellent job catering to the dietary restrictions of our guests, and some of the vegetarians said, "I'm surprised they have multiple vegetarian options that not only taste great, but taste very different from each other".  If you want to do something more memorable than the Chicken/Steak/Salmon dinner options for your wedding, go with Timber!
Good pizza  too many kids
Easily my favorite place in the neighborhood. I live near here and the breakfast is not expensive and delicious, pizza is great, small bar is chill. All around great, and staff are really nice.
Great pizza
Quality Meat and not greasy
Has a secret gluten free crust!
A perfect neighborhood pizza spot!
Nice environment, good pizza options, quick service (it was busy), good pricing and the pizza was very good. Try the place out.
Best wood fire pizza in DC. Definitely worth a trip to Petworth or as a neighborhood local, a weekly hangout. Great bar service and outdoor setting available.
So-so for vegetarians. Regular pies without meat are pretty dry without the meat grease. Also, check the order twice before leaving the shop. Good empanadas tho!
(Translated by Google) Rich but somewhat expensive pizzas  (Original) Pizzas ricas aunque algo caras
Awesome food

Hands down one of the best pizzas in the city. Crust is amazing, light, thin and crispy. The sauce, which to me is one of the most important pieces of a pizza, is bright and flavorful, and all the toppings I’ve tried are super fresh. Try the pineapple hot sauce stuff they have too, it’s an interesting kick.  Long lines can be intimidating but trust me, it’s well worth the wait or picking it up for take home. Just eat it quick because the pies are fresh and made to order!

We had an excellent salad...  Empanadas...  Two pizzas...  All were worthy of eating again. This place is pleasant to be in and the staff was lovely as can be. Would definitely recommend without hesitation...
Great salad and pizza

Pizza was great!  Space was a problem, so they probably need to expand soon.  But space being a problem can be a good indicator that of an establishments quality and service.  The staff was friendly and helpful trying to find seating.  They have good local craft beer selection too!  So, be cognizant of the crowd and don't camp if they are busy.  Because the service is quick, it is on you too move your butt if you are done!

Good pizza, wood fired oven right there for everyone to see, too. I tried the cheese pizza and that alone was about a 7.2. The dough was just a little doughy. Not sure why, it didn't seem like there was too much sauce or cheese. The flavors were all solid though so 7.2 is a fair score. The other pizzas that I tried were better, the pesto sauce was good and the combos they made were delicious. Their salad was also delicious as well. I went on a hot summer day and the inside still felt cool and nice, their ventilation/exhaust system was on point.

It was ooookaaayyyy. The dough wasn't cooked all the way through and there were too many gimmicks. Too many sauces with too many spices covering up the flavor of the dough, the sauce (I had red sauce which I did really like) and the cheese. Everything was just over flavored, but not in a way that was enjoyable for me. My teenage son (who fancies himself a chef and pizza is his specialty) was with me.  The whole dinner, he kept mumbling..."meh". Service was great though and I love the community tables! We also had salad and pork empanadas. Same complaint - too gimmicky.
Very good pizza. A little pricey.
Excellent service and super tasty food. Great atmosphere.
A Brooklyn pizza restaurant, right here in DC. Really great quality all around, and fun topping combinations to boot. Seating can be a bit of a wait, but it’s well worth it.
The dough its perfect!

The pizza crust is hands down one of the best I've eaten in my brief time as a grown fetus. The toppings, however crazy they may sound, come together to form an extremely complex and satisfying taste profile (see "kale pizza"). A solid entry in the malcolm time spent in DC. 5 malcolms out of 5
Great place to eat at when in D.C.
Really nice pizza, good vibe.  Felt a little rushed as pizza arrived so quickly

I am overall very confused by this restaurant. It seems to be a pizzeria mixed with a Mexican bar mixed with a bagel shop, and the decor reflects all of these. The food is fine, but the drinks are too expensive.

Went for dinner and was not disappointed! Definitely worth the 2019 Michelin bib gourmand based off the great taste and interesting beer menu. It won’t just be your standard Blue Moon in stock! Even the beer menu delights with some good picks.
Delicious pizza and good breakfast - bagels, empanadas, and biscuits. It does get very busy on weekends and there can be a long line.
Best pizza I know on earth.

Great pizza! Even arriving 15 minutes after they opened there was a line out the door. Don't forget to read the sign-order first and then sit down. If there aren't available seats, there is a waitlist so it's not first come first served on seating.  I encourage doing half pies of flavors so you can try a few if you go with other people. Draft list looked pretty interesting, and they have an assortment of cans available as well.

Went back for dinner... The pizza is solid. For this area they do good work. Two Amy's and Pupatella still have a leg up.  Breakfast: Quick egg empanada before they closed for the afternoon. They were eggsalent, yet a tad small, and a little overpriced.  Very strange hours here. They stop food service early afternoon on Saturday - 1:00 PM.  I saw many people trying to get into the restaurant for a late lunch 1:00ish but they were done until dinner. I feel like they are missing some major opportunity here.  Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz

Delicious pizza with fresh ingredients cooked to perfection in a brick oven, with good selection of local beers and freshly-mixed drinks at the bar. Ordering at the counter means the line goes out the door, but it moves quickly, so don't worry.

1st time having Timber and this is hands down my favorite Pizza that I've ever had in my life! And what wonderful customer service do they have! You know what makes great food even better? Great friendly customer service! Big things up to Timber!
We visited from FL, great vibe...great food...highly recommend
Helpful and courteous staff. Pizzas are delicious.
Fun place. Great staff. Great pizza. Drinks were ok. I would go back.
Pretty good pizza!
Fat service
Believe the hype! Their pizza is legit!
The Bentley is definitely among top pizzas I’ve ever had
Pizza was amazing, although there is very little place to sit down and eat. If we waited, that would have been long, we decided to eat in the car so the waiting time was 10 minutes!
Pizza is fantastic, service is great

Tiny, blistery, black bubbles on a delicately crispy, pillowy base.  Tomato sauce with balanced tartness, flavorful pesto, sharp cheese blended into the mozz. Great pizza! Friendly service, nice vibe, good beer selection. Will definitely be back for more!

Certainly one of the best pizza joints in DC, the crust is airy for amount of dough, but the sauce is outstanding, combining to give a delicious base for a good range of toppings and number of creative pies that make it a go-to pizzeria. The selection of local beers and ciders complimented the food nicely. Will definitely go back.

Good to see food bringing people together in an area that looks like it needs it. They carry Victoria (beer); it shows that someone is being real thoughtful when crafting their alcohol selection.  Although they take no reservations, and the line can often be out the door on weekend nights, their seating system works well enough. If it was a tad larger, and could afford some patio space I'd feel like I'm back in Atlanta at Antico.  The pizza is fantastic as well, by the way.
Absolutely awesome pizza, empanadas, and ice cream.  Loved this place and will be back!!!
Delicious pizza. Alcohol prices are absurd. If you're going to charge $10 for a 10oz can of cider you should let customers know up front they are getting ripped off.
Great pizza, great atmosphere

Finally had the chance to stop by today at Timber pizza company. What they showed on Instagram definitely delivered. Their empanadas were amazing with brisket inside pair with a sweet sauce. Their pizza was amazing also, very tasty cheese , fresh ingredients. Next time I’m gonna try a green pizza; they look delicious also
BEST pizza in DC! 🍕🍕🍕🍕🍕
Amazing!
Love timbers pizza sooooo much!
Great service
New taste in Pizza

Empanadas were out of this world, but you're probably going here for pizza. This pizza is interesting, it has a similar look to New Haven apizza, a nice char, but it's char stops in the middle, a symptom of undercooking the pizza resulting in too much flop.  Atmosphere was nice.

Great pizza and service! The place is tiny, but these folks know what they're doing and they've got a system in place.  The pizza isn't full on neapolitan style,  but a little crisper and thinner crust, which really is so much better.  Theres a dozen neapolitan pizza restaurants in DC, but Timber sets themselves apart by doing things a little different.  Pizza was so good, I came back to try breakfast and their bagels were awesome!
Not only the pizza is great, maybe the best in dc area, the service is awesome, the place is always packed but their organization is awesome, you don't have to wait too long, and they have great bee
Friendly people and good food. Breakfast is tasty!
Make sure to try green monster even if veggies aren't your favorite!

This pizza was amazing, I will definitely be back. They let you do half and half if you can't decide on which pizza to get. I got half the Bentley and half the Penelope. The honey on the Bentley brings it an amazing touch. One of the best neopolitan pizzas I've ever had.
Great pizza, good times
Timber pizza did a fabulous job of catering our team party.  The food was great and the service was stellar!!
I stopped by for dinner on Monday and was pleasantly surprised to discover the pizza was discounted pizza night! We got two pizzas, everything was delicious!
Great pizza toppings, outside sitting area, bar in the back, and most importantly great pizza crust.
Amazing pizza! Thin crust and various not standard toppings.

The best pizza I've had in the DMV! If you plan to dine in, be prepared for a bit of a wait as the dining room is fairly small. We ordered to-go, and our pizzas were done very quickly despite it being a busy Saturday night. The staff is also super friendly!
It was crowded, but we were seated faster than anticipated. The pizza was delicious!
Sometimes you have to wait a while, but the Bentley is delicious. Good selections of beers, but no Bud Light or Coors Light.
The best. Not really much else to say.
Small place but Fantastic Pizzas and Empanadas. Very friendly staff. Breakfast empanadas also amazing.
Good  gourmet  pizzas
Great vegan empanadas!
Great food, great pizza, great service!

This is our favorite pizza place in DC and worth the travel time from downtown. The staff is incredibly speedy at putting out delicious pizzas and we love their cocktails and beer selection. We have dined in and taken out and have been happy every time. Do not be alarmed by the crowds on a busy night - they are great at finding you the perfect spot.
Great salads and unique pizza
Best Pizza I've had in Washington DC. Not to be missed. Worth the trip while you're in DC. The pizza is delicious! Creative flavor combinations wow your tastebuds. Yum!
Best pizza! Busy shop!
Good beer. Delicious pizza. We are having them cater our wedding and the guys who run the shop are super chill and competent so the fiance and I are pretty hyped
Very high quality pizza, would eat there again

This is my favorite pizza place in dc (20+ years of eating pizza in the District). The service is pretty good and a friendly staff but it gets crowded and line is out the door in the summer. The variety of pizzas is great and the flavor is masterful. Thin crust and great blends of sauces and cheeses. It’s not very central in dc but it’s worth the trip. The pizza will likely be a two day affair if you get your own, but any pizza is a personal pizza if you believe enough. Highly recommend!
Excellent wood-fired pizza and a decent beer selection. Limited seating, especially tough for people with mobility challenges.
Amazing food, drinks, and atmosphere. My favorite pizza in the city.
Crowded and busy but worth the wait
They have breakfast too on certain days which is as yummy as their pizza
Tasty artisanal pizzas. Great ambiance and music as well. Prices are a tad bit much for what you get, but overall worth it. Would definitely come here again!
Love this place and so happy for them growing in popularity BUT the seating has become a headache!
Amazing places, the pizza is thing, crispy, just delicious! Thanks guys we had a really good night
The best!!

Absolutely amazing!  Everything we ate was excellent.  The salad we had was subperb -- local and fresh. The pizza was the best  I have ever eaten.  Even the beer was local.  The dessert  was Timber's icecream  with homemade cones  in a word extraordinary! Finally, the staff were attentive to detail.  The food they prepared was not only tasty, it was a delight for the eyes. Authentic food!  Puts American chain restaurants to shame.

Pizza and beer were tasty and reasonably priced. Vegetarian empanadas were just okay--a little heavy on the smokiness. A small and busy restaurant. We were seated at the bar, which got a little uncomfortable toward the end of our meal when a couple people were standing right behind us and waiting for us to leave so they could take our seats.
Always a 5. Love this place
Great pizza.   Fast service.  Able to do half and half, which is rare for an "artisan pizza" joint.
Ordered from here so I can only speak about the food! Pizza was yummy, small but amazing selection of salads. I got the one with the butternut squash and the portion was very fair and filling!
Cozy, Comfortable, delicious pizza, lots of bev to choose from and very attentive crew.
Amazing breakfast

Best pizza in DC (try the Penelope!). The only thing is that the logistics inside the restaurant kind of suck. You order your pizza up front and then just have to wait and try and vulture a table as they come available, and it is not a big space. Much easier to navigate with a small group; untenable for large groups.
The pizzas were very good, not many places can make good dough but this place does it right! Same goes for the sauce. A bit of a line  but worth the wait.  Great for groups👍🏻
Best Pizza in area by far.

Oh man, I cannot wait to go back to Timber. Amazing pizza (had The Lot, and definitely try the spicy pineapple sauce), communal seating, fast service. Would write more but I'm going to go buy more pizza.
Tasty pizza in a cool spot.

Timber Pizza Company is just a fabulous dining option for pizza in Washington, DC. They have a tremendous selection of drinks, wines and beers and the ambience and atmosphere are equally cool. The service is reliably good and my one and only complaint is that I wish they stayed open later. That said, I still highly recommend Timber Pizza without hesitation.
Nice place
Best pizza in DC. Also catch their popup.
Delicious wood fired pizza. Was here for an engagement event. Food was great, spare event room needs some love. Very sparse with no decoration whatsoever.

Very fun and low-key. The pizza is quite good and pairs well with their Moscow Mule bottle. Awesome spot for pairs, larger groups will have trouble finding seating on Fridays and Saturdays. Their semi-revised seating system has made the experience a lot more pleasant.
Great pizza, great salad, great hosts.
Solid wood fired pizza, great counter service, and outdoor seating that is dog friendly.

One of the best pizzeria of Washington DC. I would highly recommended it for everyone. I would certainly visit it again. The quality and taste is excellent. They just need to decrease a bit the prices. Nevertheless, the overall experience is outstanding. The staff is friendly as well. Very nice spot!
Wow, this place. You know it's good when on a Friday night there is a line out the door.

Arguably one of the best pizzerias in the DC area.  Crust is perfectly chewy (akin to Pupatellas) with a little bit of char (if you're into that) and their tomato sauce is flavorful.  They have a tasty variety of red and white pizzas to choose from, with a surprisingly wide selection of canned beers.  Also, they have a swing seat at the window perfect for a date or young children.
Some of the best pizza in DC; no question. Cute place that can get crowded quickly. Come early and come on an off day and enjoy!
I love Timber. Always a good pie.
Love em!
Amazing wonderful friendly great vibe
Nearly perfect.  Outstanding pizza and an equally outstanding breakfast options. The small but efficient space is my only reason for not rating five stars.
Great Pizza Joint in the neighborhood!
Pizza was great! The wait wasn't too terrible, and the staff is very friendly
Honestly want to give this place fewer stars because I don’t want y’all to come crowd this amazing pizza spot.
Pizza was great. Wine was not.  Atmosphere is casual neighborhood vibe.
Yum! Great pizza joint in Petworth. Super small restaurant but they totally make up for it with their pizza and service.

Great pizza, drinks, and salads. Wait times can be long during busy hours and seating is first come first serve. All these things and it's still worth it. It's like getting 2 Amys or Menomala but in Petworth.  Breakfast/Brunch Update: Food is delicious, but don't come here late(past 930am) if you want bagels or biscuits. They are sold out of everything bagels pretty much everytime I have shown up past 9 am.
Excellent pizza. Get the Bentley.

YummmMMMmmm! I loved what I ate here. Basically, you can design your pizza from a fun assortment of sauces and toppings. They have vegan cheese for those who want that option. You can even customize halves of pizza in case you're not sure what you want to get. There's a full bar with wine & beer options, especially from local wineries and breweries. Seating is family style so prepare to get cozy, and outside seating is limited but it's also really easy to take what you want to-go.
Best Pizza I've ever had. The Bentley 🍕🍕
Cool hangout for a different kind of pizza-evening experience. Located on upshur street NW dc.
Really really good pizza. Very unique flavors. It is rather pricy though and the pizzas aren't very large. You will probably need to get at least one pizza per two people and maybe a salad.
Easily the best pizza in DC. The only place I've ever seen lines out the door.
Delicious and cozy neighborhood spot in Petworth. Good vibes and service, and was worth the trip
Definitely some of the best pizza in DC.
Nice neighborhood spot.  Gotta try the Bentley Pizza!
Very crowded and a little pricey, but extremely delicious wood-oven pizzas and empanadas.
Timber pizza is amazing. Their pizzas are unique and absolutely delicious. Great local beers and drinks are also available.
Pizza ans brunch are excellent.
great pizza and a local place to eat!
Excellent pizza. Very happy with the food and the service.
The pizza is really good. But we waited 1 hour and the people behind us got their order 30 minutes earlier.

Sunday evening last week... well you can imagine the line was out the door. My random tinder date and I had a wonderful time here. The line was out the door when we arrived to Timber. We had no fear and waited in line to order at the counter. There were a few tables I was eyeing to sit at but the completion was tough. So we decided to take the pizza back to my place, maybe that was my plan after all. Regardless.. the pizza was delicious. We had a meat lover style pizza. I forget the name, but it was perfect. The beer selection was wonderful. As we waited for the pizza we drank two cold ipas outside and had a lovely time. The pizza is thin crust and was the perfect amount to split between two people. A salad would have been nice to share. Good food and good ingredients.
Best pizza in DC
Delicious pizza and great beer selection.
Pretty basic pizza, about 20+ varieties of IPA/wheat/wit/hoppy hipster flavor beer. Everyone there seemed to like it.
Great food great service..   the awards they have received for "Best Pizza" are well deserved
Good. Can get packed but should try it if you can.
Go there for bagels in the weekend and get an Everything Chala roll. It will change your life!
Solid place to get a pizza and drink a beer.

Okay, okay, I finally went.  It's not the best slice in town but it's pretty darn good.  I went for their take on margherita on my first go because it's the easiest way to get a comparison to others, but if (read: when) I go back, I'll probably go for one of the more interesting pizzas.
Bring back The Taylor!
Good weekend breakfast place. Limited menu, but really good (no pizza in the morning, different operators of same space)
Great pie.
Great easy family breakfast on weekend mornings.  The breakfast empanadas were delicious and they had a nice range of pastries.  Fast and fun.

The best pizza I've had outside of Italy and even my Italian friend says the same! And I'm also vegan but will bend my own diet for Timber veggie pizza once in a blue moon. Their salads are also very wonderful! I love the pea shoots, pesto and flowers they use! It's wonderful! Always wonderful!

Absolutely fantastically fresh pizza!  With whole, fresh basil leaves and fresh mozzarella with thin crust, you cannot go wrong!  Ordered the Shirley with cheese, pesto, tomato, peppers, chorizo and onions and requested to hold the provolone (too sharp!) but keep the mozzarella.  They had no problems accommodating my request and the pizza turned out amazing!  Planning another trip soon!
Great pizza, big crowds
Delicious
Great food! Amazing small business!

Pizza is one of my things...and I search high and low for the best.  My journey led me here a while ago and we return again and again. Can be crowded and I very much dislike communal tables but overall a fun spot to have some pizza and meet friends.  Thin crust, creative topping combinations.
Great first visit. Enjoyed the Moscow Mule and The Shirley pizza. Friendly staff. I will return.

By far my favorite pizza place in dc. I’m a Roman pizza type of person, I’m more into the toppings than the dough, if you’re like me you’ll love this place. They’re toppings are just fantastic and the thin crust gets all crispy and smoky
It's good
This place is far better than 2amys. Enjoy creative and delicious pizzas and salads.

Was tipped to this as all-time best pizza material. We tried five different pies and it landed perfectly. Great range for red, white, and green concoctions all on a perfect dough with just enough crispness to give it character.
Great neighborhood spot. Always busy though.
I am addicted to their pizza. Weekend breakfast is great too.
I was truly excited to visit, the smell is so inviting as you walk nearby. A fun atmosphere and especially quick service, but the pizza is unremarkable, thus the lower rating.

These guys came to a 3 Stars Brewery event and i swear I can't remember tasting a pizza this good. LOVE IT. Brought some home for the wife to try but she never got a chance lol Don't tell her i wrote this!!
The best Pizza in D.C. Also some pretty solid cocktails and a good selection of beer.
How do they make their dough so delicious and perfectly chewy? All the food is amazing,  good beer selection, very chill vibe but super busy most weekends.
Odd hours, showed up for breakfast, plain biscuits were good but not 3.25 a piece good , they even charge you extra for plain old butter

Happy I found this place. The pizza is very good and the environment is super casual. I came with a friend and we enjoyed hanging out at the communal tables, sharing a salad and eating pizza. The grapefruit spritzer was also very good. I didn't bring my daughter but it is definitely kid-friendly...crowded but relaxed.
Favorite pizza! Very cozy place. Outside seating. You have to try them!
Really damn good. Great vibe. Good service & super tasty.
Good pizza. Salad was meh.
Best pizza in Petworth.
It's the real deal. Just get in early and they will find you a seat   shared tables and the best Pizza and Beer in DC
Just sat down, seems great.

The best pizza I had for a long while. It can be a bit tricky if you're looking to eat over there since it's crowded. But for take out, it's perfectly fine. Don't be discouraged by the queue. There are quite quick so it's not as bad as it seems in terms of waiting time.
Great pizza, almost like the one you eat in Italy
Yummy pizza!  Love the hip communal vibe.
Great local place. Have had pizzas, empanadas, and breakfast. All of it great. Good beer selection also.
Great breakfast pop up. Dinner can get really busy even when ordering take out. However the food here is really good, whether it's the pizzas, salads, or pastries.

Delicious pizza and really tasty salads too. It's very popular and there's not a lot of seeing,  so it's difficult to get a table. We showed up right as they were opening on a Sunday and by 5:03 nearly all the indoor seats were taken.
Yum
Just a lovely place with great food, great dranks (yes dranks), and great vibes! Best seat in the house is the swing bench!
Love their food but never able to get a table. So we order carryouts which is fine.
Amazing pizza, trendy setting. Only problem is that it's so popular it's almost always crowded!
Breakfast is underrated. Pizza is great. One of the better pizzas in NW DC, price is where you want it. (Seriously, try the breakfast)
great pizza - kinda expensive
Good pizza!

Best Pizza EVER !!!!!!!!!!!!!!
So much fun activity The employees are the best along with the absolutely amazing pizza and salads. No wonder.my son and his family eat here often. They live just a few blocks away.
Cozy restaurant with great food and friendly staff.
Absolutely love Timber Pizza! We drive downtown just to go there about once a month. The pizza is so yummy, the atmosphere is cozy and the service/team is very friendly. Order The Lot, it's the best!

We regret to have a dinner there. Employees and waiters of the Timber Pizza Company ruined our dinner. We realized that we were dumbfound. We paid tips in advance at the order process by cashier. We got bad service like Spirit Airlines. Our tips were wasted and worthless because we paid them at cashier slot. We do not recommend you to pay tips in advance. Their hospitality is like Spirit Airlines. We did not see any waiter who served us. Waiters acted like mute and deaf. Real Deaf or hearing impaired people would do better in communication that these "mute mode" waiters at Timber Pizza Company. Waiters never introduced themselves to us. Waiters turned on air chilling conditioner even outside is freezing and windy. We never heard "Thank you!" or any appreciation and we never seen any "thank you" note. Great pizza, but really rude management. Was waiting in line when the manager came in and yelled at one of the workers. So inappropriate.
The Bentley is amazing. Great pizza!! Best I’ve had in DC.
Great neighborhood pizza joint ! I enjoyed my visit. Awesome food, great atmosphere, you can still talk to each other. Very reasonable prices.
Some of the best pizza in DC
Had the opportunity to try Timber Pizza food at a function this evening where they were were catering, best shrimp ceviche and pork empanadas and the Pizzas were amazing. I highly recommend it.
One of the best pizza in DC

The pizza is awesome, the salads are huge! Get the porch swing by the window and you will get an awesome view also. The staff is focused on quality and told me the first pizza they made for me was not up to their standards. So, they made another. There is a good beer selection with lots of local options. They even go around town of you have an event. This has to be the best pizza in town and it's in a great part of the city.
The best pizza in Petworth area

Really great pizza with some unusual flavors/combinations. It's a little small inside but there are definitely places to sit, including a swing/bench at the front window. It gets really packed on Saturday evenings so be ready for a little wait. I wouldn't recommend ordering wine.
Great pizza if you can get into the place.
Best pizza joint in DC, hands down. Expect a bit of a wait as it gets quote crowded
Excellent!!!!!!!

A local DC pizzeria....thin crust dough, clever ingredients.   I loved the mix of honey with spicy sauces as one part of the unique pie.  The sauce is light in the two times I've eaten here,  perfect as it cannot over power the savory recipes.  The Bentley is yummy.   Plus I asked the hostess to choose my IPA ... so many options I couldn't choose ... and like the food .. perfect!

I dream about the Green Monster once a week.  Timber has overtaken Menomale and Paccis as my favorite pizza spot.  All pizzas here are amazing.  It’s always packed but the cool thing is that you can sit picnic style if there’s space.  Friendly staff too.
Can't beat this place, honestly.

The pizza is 100% amazing. The communal seating is annoying and hectic. To be fair, I don't really know how else you would seat people inside such a small space, but it's still annoying. Come before 7 or after 9 if you want to find a seat without waiting.

One of the best pizza places in the district. Excellent thin crust pizza with the perfect dough and the perfect toppings. The chorizo is great and really comes through on the Bentley pizza. I also recommend trying the empanadas which are small but packed with pork. They also come with a nice pineapple hot sauce to put on top.  They also serve good draft beers, mixed drinks, and an interesting and rotating selection of canned beers to try. Highly recommend trying but get there early as it gets packed and they have limited seating.
Always awesome
Great food but small place.
Absolutely some of the best pizza i have ever had. Robust, good sauce on a very tasty, fresh crust, and gooey cheese.
Cozy venue with incredible salads and local beer list. Wine on tap is a bonus. Looking forward to trying breakfast.

At first I thought of calling this place “overrated” because it already has such a fantastic reputation, but I think it earns its 10/10, top new restaurant credential. Come early in the evening for quicker service, as the line starts to …
Great atmosphere for a fantastic pizza and some drinks.  Nice and cozy on a cold evening!
Easily one of the best pizza places in DC. Only caveat is they only do personal pies, but in my experience the better pizza places in the city only do personal pies (I'm thinking comet and menomale.)

We went here for dinner with friends on Saturday night. Although the place was slammed, the staff were all super friendly & helpful. They have vegan cheese (even though it isn't listed on menu) & plenty of veggies to top your Za with

Absolutely love Timber. I live in NYC and will travel here to get a pizza when I'm back home visiting family. Fantastic atmosphere and great people working here. They also have a tasty selection of beers and drinks on the menu as well!
The best thing that has happened in Petworth in a long time.

good pizza but very tight on space.  come when it opens or be prepared to wait or order takeout
A great experience and excelent pizza!
Was ok I have had better pizza.

The menu has some interesting pizzas on it (i.e. ratatouille pizza), and changes seasonally. I would recommend choosing a more familiar pizza (i.e. margherita pizza). The pork empanadas were delicious and served nice and hot. They were a great warm-up while waiting for the pizzas. They have a nice offering of beers and ciders, too. There is not much seating inside, and it can get very busy, so it may be best to place an order for pickup. I went on Friday night and it was packed with barely enough room to order. Staff members were rushed and brusque.
Very good pizza. Unique toppings, delicious airy yet crispy crust.

A new York city girl can be hard to convince that pizza outside of NY is any good.  This is definitely a great spot for quality pizza and really interesting toppings.  Vegan cheese substitute is not bad either!
Fantastic pizza and delightful breakfast on the weekends. The bagels should not be missed.
Josh was awesome Pizza was amazing
Amazing place. Great pizza, great concept.
